&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clinical Research Nurse&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;18&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; months Fixed-Term subject to funding &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Research &amp; Development department are seeking a clinical research nurse to work in the Clinical Research Facility. This is an exciting opportunity for an enthusiastic and reliable nurse to join the research delivery team and support recruitment to phase 1, 2 and 3 commercial and NIHR research studies, including vaccine trials. The nurse should be a proactive team player with a flexible, positive approach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience of clinical research is desirable but not essential, as full training will be given. Must have current NMC registration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameChristine AdamsonJob titleLead Research NurseEmail addresschristine.adamson@chelwest.nhs.ukTelephone number0203 3155601Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Christine Adamson, Lead Research Nurse or Serge Fedele, Team Leader, CRF&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(Christine.adamson@chelwest.nhs.uk, serge.fedele@chewlest.nhs.uk)&lt;/p&gt;
